__Slice__.slice_name: Total number of commits per repository

__SqlaTable__.sql:
SELECT commit_author_name
FROM commits
GROUP BY commit_author_name
ORDER BY commit_author_name

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id, COUNT(commit_author_name) as collaborators_count FROM (
SELECT DISTINCT commit_author_name, repository_id
FROM commits
) q1
GROUP BY repository_id
ORDER BY collaborators_count DESC

SELECT
    repo,
    CASE
        WHEN day_index = 2 THEN '1 - Monday'
        WHEN day_index = 3 THEN '2 - Tuesday'
        WHEN day_index = 4 THEN '3 - Wednesday'
        WHEN day_index = 5 THEN '4 - Thursday'
        WHEN day_index = 6 THEN '5 - Friday'
        WHEN day_index = 7 THEN '6 - Saturday'
        ELSE '7 - Sunday'
    END AS day,
    CASE
        WHEN n_parents > 1 THEN 'Merge commit'
        ELSE 'Non-merge commit'
    END AS commit_type
FROM (
    SELECT
        repository_id AS repo,
        DAYOFWEEK(committer_when) AS day_index,
        ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) AS n_parents
    FROM commits
) t
select * from repositories

SELECT commit_author_email, COUNT(*) as n
FROM commits
WHERE ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) < 2
GROUP BY commit_author_email
ORDER BY n DESC

SELECT 
    SUM(1-changelog) as changelog, 
    SUM(1-readme) as readme, 
    SUM(1-notice) as notice, 
    SUM(1-license) as license,
    SUM(1-contributing) as contributing,
    SUM(1-travis) as travis,
    SUM(1-ci) as ci,
    SUM(1-dockerfile) as dockerfile
FROM (
	SELECT 
	    repository_id, 
	    SUM(changelog) != 0 as changelog, 
        SUM(readme) != 0 as readme, 
        SUM(notice) != 0 as notice, 
        SUM(license) != 0 as license,
        SUM(contributing) != 0 as contributing,
        SUM(travis) != 0 as travis,
        SUM(ci) != 0 as ci,
    	SUM(dockerfile) != 0 as dockerfile
	FROM (
	    SELECT 
	        refs.repository_id, 
	        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CHANGELOG(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS changelog,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^README(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS readme,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^NOTICE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS notice,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^LICENSE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS license,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CONTRIBUTING(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS contributing,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^\.TRAVIS\.YML' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS travis,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CI' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS ci,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^DOCKERFILE$' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS dockerfile
	    FROM refs
	    JOIN commit_files 
	    ON refs.commit_hash = commit_files.commit_hash 
	    WHERE ref_name = "refs/heads/master" 
	) q
	GROUP BY repository_id
) q2

SELECT REPLACE(JSON_EXTRACT(SPLIT(commit_author_email, '@'), '$[1]'),'"', '') as domain, COUNT(*) as n
FROM commits
WHERE commit_author_email LIKE '%%@%%'
AND ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) < 2
GROUP BY domain
ORDER BY n DESC

SELECT REPLACE(JSON_EXTRACT(SPLIT(commit_author_email, '@'), '$[1]'),'"', '') as domain, COUNT(*) as n
FROM commits
WHERE commit_author_email LIKE '%%@%%'
AND ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) < 2
GROUP BY domain
ORDER BY n DESC

__SqlMetric__.expression: (changelog + 3 * readme + 3 * notice + 3 * license + contributing + travis + ci + Dockerfile) / 14.0

__SqlaTable__.sql:
SELECT 
    SUM(changelog != 0) / COUNT(changelog)  as changelog, 
    SUM(readme != 0)  / COUNT(changelog) as readme, 
    SUM(notice != 0)  / COUNT(changelog) as notice, 
    SUM(license != 0) / COUNT(changelog) as license,
    SUM(contributing != 0) / COUNT(changelog) as contributing,
    SUM(travis != 0) / COUNT(changelog) as travis, 
    SUM(ci != 0) / COUNT(changelog) as ci, 
    SUM(dockerfile != 0) / COUNT(changelog) as dockerfile 
FROM (
    SELECT 
        SUM(changelog) as changelog, 
        SUM(readme) as readme, 
        SUM(notice) as notice, 
        SUM(license) as license,
        SUM(contributing) as contributing,
        SUM(travis) as travis,
        SUM(ci) as ci,
        SUM(dockerfile) as dockerfile
    FROM (
        SELECT 
            refs.repository_id, 
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CHANGELOG(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS changelog,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^README(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS readme,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^NOTICE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS notice,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^LICENSE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS license,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CONTRIBUTING(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS contributing,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^\.TRAVIS\.YML' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS travis,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CI' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS ci,
            CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^DOCKERFILE$' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS dockerfile
        FROM refs
        JOIN commit_files 
        ON refs.commit_hash = commit_files.commit_hash 
        WHERE ref_name = "refs/heads/master" 
    ) q
    GROUP BY repository_id
) q2

SELECT commit_author_email, COUNT(*) as n
FROM commits
WHERE ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) < 2
GROUP BY commit_author_email
ORDER BY n DESC

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id,
         commit_author_when as date_release,
         COUNT(*) as n
  FROM refs
  NATURAL JOIN commits
  WHERE ref_name LIKE 'refs/tags/v%.%.0' OR ref_name LIKE 'refs/tags/%.%.0'
  GROUP BY repository_id, date_release
  ORDER BY repository_id, date_release

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id, COUNT(file_path) as files_count
FROM refs
NATURAL JOIN commit_files
WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
GROUP BY repository_id
ORDER BY files_count DESC

SELECT
    repository_id,
    commit_author_when,
    CASE ARRAY_LENGTH(commit_parents) WHEN 0 THEN 'Commit' WHEN 1 THEN 'Commit' ELSE 'Merge' END AS commit_type
FROM commits

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id, lang
FROM (
    SELECT
        repository_id,
        LANGUAGE(file_path) as lang
    FROM refs
    NATURAL JOIN commit_files
    WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
) AS q
WHERE lang NOT IN ('', 'Ignore List')

SELECT lang, SUM(n) as sum_n
FROM (
SELECT lang, SUM(lines) as n
FROM (
SELECT f.repository_id, LANGUAGE(cf.file_path, f.blob_content) as lang,
ARRAY_LENGTH(SPLIT(f.blob_content, '\n')) as lines
FROM files AS f
NATURAL JOIN commit_files cf
NATURAL JOIN refs
WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
AND file_path NOT LIKE 'vendor/%%'
) AS t
WHERE lang IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY repository_id, lang
) AS t
GROUP by lang
ORDER BY n DESC

SELECT lang, COUNT(*) as n
FROM (
SELECT LANGUAGE(cf.file_path, f.blob_content) as lang
FROM files AS f
NATURAL JOIN commit_files cf
NATURAL JOIN refs
WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
AND file_path NOT LIKE 'vendor/%%'
) AS t
WHERE lang is not null
GROUP BY lang
ORDER BY 2 DESC

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repo,
commit_author_when commit_date,
COUNT(*) as n
FROM commits
WHERE commit_author_when <= now()
GROUP BY repo, commit_date
ORDER BY repo, commit_date

SELECT commit_author_when,
COUNT(*) as n
FROM ref_commits
NATURAL JOIN commits
WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
GROUP BY commit_author_when
ORDER BY commit_author_when

SELECT 
    REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(changelog) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as changelog, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(readme) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as readme, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(notice) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as notice, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(license) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as license,
    CASE WHEN MAX(contributing) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as contributing,
    CASE WHEN MAX(travis) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as travis, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(ci) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as ci, 
    CASE WHEN MAX(dockerfile) = 0 THEN 'missing' ELSE '' END as dockerfile
FROM (
    SELECT 
        refs.repository_id, 
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CHANGELOG(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS changelog,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^README(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS readme,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^NOTICE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS notice,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^LICENSE(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS license,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CONTRIBUTING(|\.MD)' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS contributing,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^\.TRAVIS\.YML' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS travis,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^CI' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS ci,
        CASE WHEN file_path REGEXP '(?i)^DOCKERFILE$' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS dockerfile
    FROM refs
    JOIN commit_files 
    ON refs.commit_hash = commit_files.commit_hash 
    WHERE ref_name = "refs/heads/master" 
) q
GROUP BY repository_id

SELECT REPLACE(repository_id, 'github.com/', '') as repository_id, COUNT(*) as n
FROM ref_commits
WHERE ref_name = 'HEAD'
GROUP BY repository_id
ORDER BY n DESC
LIMIT 20
